OL,3,CMeet Hugo the underwater hoover
OL,4,Ckeeping a Guernsey harbour spotless
OL,6,FThe hoover was bought by the Rotary
OL,7,FGuernesiais for #8,000 as part of a
OL,8,Fproject with Guernsey Ports.
OL,10,FIt is hoped that Hugo can continue
OL,11,Fkeeping Victoria Marina spotless for
OL,12,Fthe next ten years.
OL,14,FHelen Salisbury, president of the
OL,15,FRotary Guernesiais, told ITV News:
OL,16,F"It's collecting things as little as a
OL,17,Fpostage stamp. Crisp wrappers, plastic
OL,18,Fbottles - all of the things that
OL,19,Funfortunately end up in the water.
